    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Secretary of State to the
                            Acting Secretary of State
                    
                    Secretary of State Byrnes was in Paris for the
                        meeting of the Council of Foreign Ministers which took place April 25–May
                        15.</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1946v05</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d617</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">617</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1946-05-02T11:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1946-05-02T11:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-05-02T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-05-02T11:00:00-05:00" n="617" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d617">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">865.51/5–246: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="43" xml:id="d617fn43">Secretary of State Byrnes was in Paris for the
                        meeting of the Council of Foreign Ministers which took place April 25–May
                        15.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-05-02T17:00:00+01:00">May 2, 1946—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 10:08 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2108. <gloss target="#t_Delsec1">Delsec</gloss> 454 from the Secretary. Your
                        <gloss target="#t_Secdel1">Secdel</gloss> 2004, May 1, noon.<note n="44" xml:id="d617fn44">Not printed.</note> I perceive no reason to delay proposed
                    Exim bank loan to Italy or prompt consideration of Italian application for fund
                    and bank membership at early May meeting.<note n="45" xml:id="d617fn45">In the
                        meeting of the National Advisory Council of May 7, “Mr. Clayton said he
                        would like to bring up the question of a loan to Italy. Secretary Byrnes had
                        informed them that nothing had happened which would make him want to
                        postpone consideration of the loan. He suggested another meeting within the
                        next couple of days.” (Item 5, Minutes, <gloss target="#t_NAC1">N.A.C.</gloss> meeting, Lot 60–D 137: Box 1)</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
